Dialogue: 5,0:00:55.96,0:00:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Jo{\fscx164}-{\fscx82}Johnny!?
Dialogue: 5,0:01:07.67,0:01:09.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:12.50,0:01:16.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 5,0:01:23.79,0:01:27.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Takizawa?
Dialogue: 5,0:01:35.78,0:01:38.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna give him a good smacking.
Dialogue: 5,0:01:42.58,0:01:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong, sir?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:11.73,0:04:15.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you shouldn't be wearing that shirt around...
Dialogue: 5,0:04:15.73,0:04:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it. I think I get why Seleção II wanted me to wear it now.
Dialogue: 5,0:04:39.50,0:04:43.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iinuma Akira, correct?
Dialogue: 5,0:04:43.46,0:04:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 5,0:04:52.93,0:04:58.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Iinuma Seijiro's wife, Iinuma Chigusa.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:22.36,0:05:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you? And how are you connected to yesterday's missile incident?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:28.19,0:05:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Missile incident?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:30.34,0:05:34.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right, I think I'm one of the people it was targeting.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:34.89,0:05:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:36.99,0:05:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're admitting you're one of the terrorists.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:41.48,0:05:42.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What!?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:42.89,0:05:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The government has announced that last night's incident
Dialogue: 5,0:05:46.00,0:05:51.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was a preemptive attack on the terrorists who perpetrated Careless Monday.
Dialogue: 5,0:05:51.45,0:05:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why have they done that!?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:55.20,0:05:58.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this another part of Mononobe's request?
Dialogue: 5,0:05:58.28,0:06:05.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, your existence is nothing but an insult to Iinuma Seijiro.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:06.26,0:06:12.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even after Iinuma was brought down by infighting, he stood up for this country again,
Dialogue: 5,0:06:12.82,0:06:16.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and died with patriotism still burning in his heart.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:16.27,0:06:24.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show the world all of your misdeeds, starting with claiming to be Iinuma Seijiro's illegitimate son!
Dialogue: 5,0:06:26.33,0:06:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm having your DNA tested.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:43.73,0:06:47.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. Looks like I can't stay with you for now.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:48.70,0:06:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway...
Dialogue: 5,0:06:50.03,0:06:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a favor I need to ask.
Dialogue: 5,0:06:55.48,0:06:57.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you find my mom?
Dialogue: 5,0:06:58.98,0:07:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I met her on Careless Monday.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:03.56,0:07:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it was somewhere around Aomono-Yokochō.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:06.92,0:07:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One of the people I evacuated was a woman with a mameshiba dog.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:11.22,0:07:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure it was mom.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:14.07,0:07:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then that dog{\fscx164}-{\fscx82}
Dialogue: 5,0:07:18.35,0:07:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When she realized it was me, she got flustered and ran away, leaving it behind.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:24.23,0:07:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I checked the evacuation point later, but I couldn't find her.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:28.79,0:07:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you have your memories back, Takizawa!?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:33.47,0:07:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, at least of being Takizawa Akira.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:36.63,0:07:39.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, can you do that for me?
Dialogue: 5,0:07:41.40,0:07:42.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll try.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:42.60,0:07:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for taking care of it for me.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:45.69,0:07:46.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:47.40,0:07:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I almost forgot.
Dialogue: 5,0:07:53.36,0:07:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 5,0:07:55.45,0:07:58.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A memento of our time in New York.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:00.79,0:08:02.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll keep in touch.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:28.23,0:08:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saki!
Dialogue: 5,0:08:32.58,0:08:34.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Takizawa?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:34.13,0:08:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prime Minister Iinuma's backers took him somewhere.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:39.08,0:08:42.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At least it means the media didn't pick up on it.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:42.88,0:08:44.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what are they doing here?
Dialogue: 5,0:08:45.80,0:08:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like they've been waiting here since the news leaked a couple days ago.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:50.90,0:08:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, let's get out of here.
Dialogue: 5,0:08:53.16,0:08:56.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're pretty famous now too.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:02.33,0:09:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to tell Hirasawa about Takizawa's mother too.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:06.43,0:09:07.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:07.57,0:09:11.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're going to use your phone, download AirShip first.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:11.73,0:09:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a VoIP program Itazu made.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:15.53,0:09:19.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their phones are being tapped by the Public Security Intelligence Agency.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:19.18,0:09:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should use it if you need to contact them.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:21.55,0:09:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tapped?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:23.20,0:09:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems like the police are intent on pinning the missile attacks on Eden of the East.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:33.18,0:09:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'm gonna go get the car.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:43.96,0:09:45.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:45.05,0:09:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saki?
Dialogue: 5,0:09:47.36,0:09:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:49.26,0:09:52.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried when you took so long to call.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:52.43,0:09:53.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about Takizawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.83,0:09:59.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:09:59.07,0:10:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:00.81,0:10:04.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't use the Eden System now, though.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:04.69,0:10:08.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to have to use the old system we left at school.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:10.87,0:10:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you the password to get in.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:13.50,0:10:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:15.64,0:10:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll keep in touch.
Dialogue: 5,0:10:17.52,0:10:19.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, next...
Dialogue: 5,0:10:29.79,0:10:31.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:32.41,0:10:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saki? What's up?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:35.56,0:10:38.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're back already?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:42.47,0:10:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, you want me to come now?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:45.65,0:10:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:47.16,0:10:50.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you want me to bring the dog?
Dialogue: 5,0:10:50.76,0:10:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, you know what time we have to open in the morning.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:00.65,0:11:02.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:03.44,0:11:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will they bring her?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:05.10,0:11:06.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:06.05,0:11:07.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:07.96,0:11:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I tried an image search.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:11.90,0:11:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:19.62,0:11:23.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A request for the PSIA to investigate Eden of the East?
Dialogue: 5,0:11:23.16,0:11:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh man.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:25.18,0:11:28.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mononobe's going after Juiz again, too.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:33.08,0:11:36.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kuroha protected her once,
Dialogue: 5,0:11:36.63,0:11:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but if I don't do it myself this time, I won't be able to save anyone.
Dialogue: 5,0:11:47.02,0:11:52.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do I do? If I use Juiz, I'll get found out.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:02.27,0:12:03.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okada!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:04.09,0:12:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, Takizawa!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:06.27,0:12:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I finally found you!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:08.61,0:12:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me go!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:09.43,0:12:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right now I'm Iinuma Akira...
Dialogue: 5,0:12:12.07,0:12:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I didn't know that!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:13.56,0:12:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell do you think you're doing going from being Air King to the Prime Minister's son!?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:17.60,0:12:22.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You even dragged us to the airport. What are you up to now!?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:22.20,0:12:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is gonna be another sausage party, isn't it!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:25.61,0:12:29.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, are you one of the 20,000 NEETs?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:29.23,0:12:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,II gathered you here or something?
Dialogue: 5,0:12:33.25,0:12:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about!? You screwed us over!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:37.90,0:12:43.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd be happier as part of the AKX20000, but now I'm just a freeter!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:43.99,0:12:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was better off as a NEET.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:47.03,0:12:48.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take responsibility!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:49.47,0:12:52.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure that one wasn't my fault...
Dialogue: 5,0:12:52.62,0:12:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes it was!
Dialogue: 5,0:12:54.58,0:12:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine, fine.
Dialogue: 5,0:12:56.89,0:13:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you do one more thing for me, then?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:03.20,0:13:05.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to make things interesting again, aren't you.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:07.96,0:13:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kind of.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:13.27,0:13:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long are you going to keep us waiting?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:15.68,0:13:20.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry it up, the media and the NEETs are already all over.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:25.56,0:13:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it. Cover your face like that.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:45.62,0:13:49.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've sent Takizawa the AirShip installer.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:49.96,0:13:51.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's new stuff showing up in his history.
Dialogue: 5,0:13:54.22,0:13:58.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this? Business cards and an office rental?
Dialogue: 5,0:13:58.39,0:14:01.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An election strategy from a marketing agency?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:01.95,0:14:03.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's more.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:03.99,0:14:09.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's cozying up to all of the major parties, and doing favors for major politicians and financiers.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:09.72,0:14:12.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, he's serious.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:12.37,0:14:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he getting ready for a debut as a hereditary politician?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:18.40,0:14:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takizawa...
Dialogue: 5,0:14:20.16,0:14:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 5,0:14:21.72,0:14:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:23.17,0:14:25.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saki called earlier.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:25.09,0:14:30.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you know more about what's going on here than I do.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:30.05,0:14:32.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like with yesterday's missiles.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:33.06,0:14:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:34.45,0:14:39.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If XI hadn't taken it for me, it would've been game over.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:39.56,0:14:43.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't just let this game end yet.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:43.49,0:14:46.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to save my Juiz somehow.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:46.03,0:14:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:47.53,0:14:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like our fate is tied to yours anyway.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:52.26,0:14:58.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll put you on to the man closest to the answer you seek.
Dialogue: 5,0:14:59.81,0:15:02.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Sup, Vintage. You chill?
Dialogue: 5,0:15:02.58,0:15:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Itazu! It's been a while.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:06.21,0:15:08.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's can the small talk.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:08.57,0:15:15.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I checked out XII's account, and it's showin' gas and expenses for a driver,
Dialogue: 5,0:15:15.43,0:15:19.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I didn't realize he was gonna drive in circles forever.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:19.81,0:15:25.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This probably would've meant that SOB with the slicked-back hair, I, would've beat us to the punch,
Dialogue: 5,0:15:25.29,0:15:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I've been keepin' an eye on them since last night with the Chuo Expressway cameras.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:30.27,0:15:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a couple trailers I thought wandered off,
Dialogue: 5,0:15:32.88,0:15:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I picked 'em up in convoy heading inbound a couple hours back.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:38.12,0:15:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, you're awesome!
Dialogue: 5,0:15:40.64,0:15:42.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No shit.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:42.29,0:15:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And trailer IX just took the Kawasaki-Ukishima exit.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:48.26,0:15:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we look at how long they've been on the road,
Dialogue: 5,0:15:51.20,0:15:55.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they're probably gonna stop for gas and to switch drivers any time now.
Dialogue: 5,0:15:55.30,0:15:56.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means...
Dialogue: 5,0:15:56.85,0:16:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Juiz's next destination is probably Umihotaru.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:00.51,0:16:01.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umihotaru?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:02.91,0:16:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks that way.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:04.47,0:16:05.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 5,0:16:05.71,0:16:07.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you gonna do now?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:07.88,0:16:10.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go check out Umihotaru.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:10.64,0:16:14.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without Juiz, I'm just an amnesiac normal guy.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:16.13,0:16:19.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're a normal guy, what are we?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:19.85,0:16:24.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're really something special. The PSIA being after you just proves it.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:24.54,0:16:29.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be pretty tough getting caught up in something like this alone.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:29.88,0:16:33.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But from here on we'll share the burden.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:33.13,0:16:35.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm prepared to share your fate.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:35.59,0:16:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to Umihotaru. Let's rendezvous there.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:39.51,0:16:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure?
Dialogue: 5,0:16:40.95,0:16:45.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you get any deeper, you won't be able to go back to your old lives.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:45.49,0:16:47.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's my line.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:47.55,0:16:51.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sick of being a NEET anyway.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:54.27,0:16:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 5,0:16:55.64,0:16:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's meet at Umihotaru.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:14.25,0:17:15.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:24.45,0:17:26.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can show your face now.
Dialogue: 5,0:17:30.42,0:17:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tadah!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:36.70,0:17:40.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx164}-{\fscx82}It worked! Look at what I pulled off!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:36.70,0:17:38.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx164}-{\fscx82}Who are you!?
Dialogue: 5,0:17:42.30,0:17:44.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm{\fscx164}-{\fscx82}
Dialogue: 5,0:17:50.15,0:17:53.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you come back, you'll never find me!
Dialogue: 5,0:17:53.25,0:17:55.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Serves you right!
Dialogue: 5,0:18:13.77,0:18:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 5,0:18:19.88,0:18:22.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, traffic was horrible.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:22.78,0:18:26.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you're busy, but you should come home sometimes.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:27.79,0:18:29.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's your dog.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:35.42,0:18:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll explain this all later.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:39.09,0:18:41.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:42.94,0:18:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:48.54,0:18:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just glad you've finally found your calling.
Dialogue: 5,0:18:56.74,0:19:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, you're always such a quick worker.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:00.36,0:19:05.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, it's time for what we talked about. Be sure to give him a warm welcome.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:05.49,0:19:07.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:07.55,0:19:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He may look like a dick, but he knows his stuff.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:11.00,0:19:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give it to him, okay?
Dialogue: 5,0:19:15.03,0:19:18.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah, yeah. Just like that.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:18.75,0:19:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks a ton.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:28.72,0:19:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Give it another shot, Outside!"
Dialogue: 5,0:19:31.68,0:19:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"His shirt seems to state that the succession of missile attacks came from outside the country."
Dialogue: 5,0:19:37.81,0:19:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"This is nothing more than a continuation of Iinumaism, often ridiculed as a right-wing movement."
Dialogue: 5,0:19:42.96,0:19:45.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go, now it's getting serious.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:45.70,0:19:53.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you meant those shirts for Mr. Outside, no one else thinks so, IX.
Dialogue: 5,0:19:57.88,0:20:00.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, gimme a break.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:00.19,0:20:01.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weren't you sleeping?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:02.51,0:20:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're still going, even without your Juiz?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:06.56,0:20:10.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm staking my pride on this fight.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:10.30,0:20:12.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:12.93,0:20:17.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I made the arrangements. You should get going.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:18.41,0:20:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's some money and the address of where I'd like you to go.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:22.66,0:20:24.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:24.08,0:20:26.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pay you back someday.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:26.49,0:20:29.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 5,0:20:36.30,0:20:37.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:54.99,0:20:57.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Annie!?
Dialogue: 5,0:20:59.41,0:21:02.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You came back!
Dialogue: 5,0:21:08.09,0:21:10.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So her name is Angelika?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:13.09,0:21:16.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Isn't it a beautiful name?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:18.88,0:21:23.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, you think I'm the mother of that missile terrorist?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:23.90,0:21:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:26.75,0:21:29.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, think about it.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:29.01,0:21:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He only lived with his mother in New York until age five, right?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:33.58,0:21:37.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't rely on childhood memories like that.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:37.52,0:21:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why'd you run away and leave her behind on Careless Monday?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:43.93,0:21:46.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ran because I was told to run.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:46.85,0:21:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It saved my life, but my home was destroyed.
Dialogue: 5,0:21:54.08,0:21:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But did you live in New York?
Dialogue: 5,0:21:56.34,0:21:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For a while. A vacation, but a long one.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:00.04,0:22:02.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And did you stay at the Gramercy?
Dialogue: 5,0:22:02.46,0:22:04.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:04.47,0:22:07.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was a theatre called Angelika nearby.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:07.63,0:22:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The same name as your dog.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:09.55,0:22:11.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that just a coincidence?
Dialogue: 5,0:22:12.34,0:22:13.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:16.04,0:22:18.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have children?
Dialogue: 5,0:22:20.87,0:22:22.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had one.
Dialogue: 5,0:22:22.98,0:22:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When?
Dialogue: 5,0:22:33.22,0:22:38.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said his mother abandoned him in Japan at age five...
Dialogue: 5,0:22:40.58,0:22:43.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was given some small change,
Dialogue: 5,0:22:43.11,0:22:48.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and then when he turned around from the department store register, his mother was gone.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:05.52,0:23:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you mind if I use your bathroom?
Dialogue: 5,0:23:09.19,0:23:10.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's over there.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:26.56,0:23:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's her. She used to be hot.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:31.49,0:23:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that man behind her{\fscx164}-{\fscx82}!
Dialogue: 5,0:23:39.98,0:23:41.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saki.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:41.64,0:23:42.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:44.98,0:23:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is{\fscx164}-{\fscx82}!
Dialogue: 5,0:23:46.45,0:23:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I think it's her when she was younger.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:49.19,0:23:51.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And look behind her.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:52.86,0:23:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prime Minister Iinuma!
Dialogue: 5,0:23:55.83,0:23:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I think so.
Dialogue: 5,0:23:58.62,0:24:00.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 5,0:24:00.45,0:24:06.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking at this, maybe Takizawa being Iinuma Seijiro's illegitimate son
Dialogue: 5,0:24:06.25,0:24:10.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,isn't just something Juiz made up.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:17.48,0:24:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At first...
Dialogue: 5,0:24:19.92,0:24:23.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that this could all be cleared up
Dialogue: 5,0:24:23.48,0:24:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by having the PSIA capture the terrorist who launched the missiles and his friends.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:28.05,0:24:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:30.03,0:24:34.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you arrange it with that phone from Ato?
Dialogue: 5,0:24:34.70,0:24:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since he's been back, I've also heard the rumor that he's really Iinuma's son.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:42.20,0:24:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 5,0:24:43.87,0:24:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And those T-shirts have certainly caught the eyes of many junior officers.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:50.36,0:24:55.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As the son of a hawkish PM, perhaps he would have access to missiles.
Dialogue: 5,0:24:55.84,0:25:00.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll check it all out. No need to worry.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:00.27,0:25:02.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mononobe.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:02.31,0:25:07.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About the proposals to raise the estate tax to 100% and reestablish the Home Ministry.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:07.72,0:25:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I intend to support them.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:10.96,0:25:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:12.74,0:25:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps it's time for extreme measures.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:22.26,0:25:23.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe that.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:28.19,0:25:31.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, this is Mononobe.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:31.09,0:25:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a chance that Iinuma Seijiro may have had a mistress around twenty years ago.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:37.28,0:25:39.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you check it out?
Dialogue: 5,0:25:44.95,0:25:46.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:25:46.67,0:25:50.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find that out during your investigation in New York?
Dialogue: 5,0:25:54.56,0:26:00.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that means Iinuma himself must have continued to pay for the hotel.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:00.63,0:26:05.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was kept reserved until half a year ago, when that man appeared.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:05.70,0:26:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood. I'll leave it to you.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:11.84,0:26:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Juiz. Put me through to the National Tax Agency.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:21.06,0:26:23.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umihotaru?
Dialogue: 5,0:26:29.47,0:26:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's from Grandfather.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:34.39,0:26:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are the trailer drivers?
Dialogue: 5,0:26:36.70,0:26:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're on break.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:39.49,0:26:42.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a nonstop trip from Yamanashi.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:42.03,0:26:44.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like we get a break either.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:45.29,0:26:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did Grandfather have to say?
Dialogue: 5,0:26:48.12,0:26:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't want to stop how the game's developing,
Dialogue: 5,0:26:53.04,0:26:54.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so we're to continue as usual.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:54.94,0:26:58.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're to fulfill any request.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:58.09,0:26:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we knew that already.
Dialogue: 5,0:26:59.80,0:27:02.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, we're not Seleção or Juiz,
Dialogue: 5,0:27:02.95,0:27:05.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just ball girls.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:05.15,0:27:06.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 5,0:27:06.82,0:27:11.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what if I requests a missile attack?
Dialogue: 5,0:27:11.60,0:27:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll kill us!
Dialogue: 5,0:27:14.65,0:27:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we should just hide those somewhere.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:20.80,0:27:22.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:22.29,0:27:24.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's against Grandfather's rules.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:25.20,0:27:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I don't think I will launch a missile {\i1}here{\i0}{\fscx32} {\r}.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:38.94,0:27:40.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 5,0:27:40.17,0:27:42.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that Seleção IX?
Dialogue: 5,0:27:43.82,0:27:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it is!
Dialogue: 5,0:28:00.17,0:28:01.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Juiz.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:01.63,0:28:05.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,IX. It seems like you're in the specified area.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:06.97,0:28:08.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:12.84,0:28:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest, I'm right by your side. Can't you tell?
Dialogue: 5,0:28:19.07,0:28:24.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not actually equipped with visual sensors, so...
Dialogue: 5,0:28:25.18,0:28:29.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aww, and here I thought I'd surprise you.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:29.03,0:28:30.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:30.27,0:28:31.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:31.88,0:28:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to apologize.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:33.44,0:28:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've finally met, now.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:36.86,0:28:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,IX. Why did you come to see me?
Dialogue: 5,0:28:41.32,0:28:45.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to save you from a missile attack.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:45.64,0:28:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know that?
Dialogue: 5,0:28:47.50,0:28:48.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:28:48.70,0:28:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And how will you protect me from the missiles?
Dialogue: 5,0:28:51.95,0:28:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't really thought of that part yet.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:00.75,0:29:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I moved his trailer.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:06.99,0:29:09.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he's trying to steal away his own Juiz?
Dialogue: 5,0:29:15.79,0:29:17.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Juiz.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:17.18,0:29:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you make me able to drive a semi?
Dialogue: 5,0:29:20.56,0:29:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know, like in The Matrix.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:23.92,0:29:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you already have every license they issue, from motorcycles to semis.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:31.45,0:29:33.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 5,0:29:35.32,0:29:37.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, I guess.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:37.09,0:29:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I just had a great idea, Juiz.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:48.45,0:29:50.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,IX too?
Dialogue: 5,0:29:50.25,0:29:52.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's not in his history.
Dialogue: 5,0:29:52.85,0:29:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's driving it himself?
Dialogue: 5,0:29:55.48,0:30:01.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see, he's following I's trailer so he can't be bombed.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:01.19,0:30:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew IX was smart!
Dialogue: 5,0:30:06.15,0:30:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do?
Dialogue: 5,0:30:07.91,0:30:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do we tell Grandfather?
Dialogue: 5,0:30:10.62,0:30:13.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's against the rules too.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:13.02,0:30:16.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't use Juiz for this,
Dialogue: 5,0:30:16.47,0:30:19.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so the other Seleção don't get to know.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:19.83,0:30:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's Grandfather, the rules still apply.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:23.64,0:30:25.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:29.40,0:30:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, you're driving Juiz!?
Dialogue: 5,0:30:32.35,0:30:37.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. I think I's going to keep things within the city, but...
Dialogue: 5,0:30:37.08,0:30:39.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you guys?
Dialogue: 5,0:30:40.98,0:30:43.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in a tunnel.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:43.94,0:30:47.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? I am too.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:47.92,0:30:51.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, maybe you're in the next one over.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:55.41,0:30:59.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When we reach Umihotaru, we'll call back.
Dialogue: 5,0:30:59.84,0:31:01.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You heard him.
Dialogue: 5,0:31:02.57,0:31:06.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hijacking Juiz? He never changes.
Dialogue: 5,0:31:06.52,0:31:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,III ordered sweets for Saizo?
Dialogue: 5,0:31:11.37,0:31:16.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saizo... Ato Saizo!?
Dialogue: 5,0:31:28.42,0:31:32.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Were Yuuki here, I'd have already sent him to meet you.
Dialogue: 5,0:31:37.05,0:31:41.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Juiz. I'd like to arrange a message to this cafe.
Dialogue: 5,0:31:54.25,0:31:58.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not Japanese anymore, am I.
Dialogue: 5,0:31:59.69,0:32:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You two.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:01.37,0:32:04.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm closing up soon, but do you two want to stick around?
Dialogue: 5,0:32:04.77,0:32:06.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 5,0:32:06.12,0:32:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two more mango lassis, then.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:15.25,0:32:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like you brought trouble along with you.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:20.99,0:32:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think they're just here for a drink, though.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:28.92,0:32:30.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:30.29,0:32:31.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, sure.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:31.94,0:32:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I was thinking the same thing.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:38.47,0:32:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The details implied she was in Tokyo,
Dialogue: 5,0:32:42.17,0:32:45.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it looks like III is really in Fukuoka.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:47.11,0:32:49.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's up, Kasuga?
Dialogue: 5,0:32:49.51,0:32:55.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master. The PSIA may have had us from the start.
Dialogue: 5,0:32:56.82,0:33:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until a few years ago, a radical student group called the Revolutionary Alliance used this room.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:02.93,0:33:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put that together with our current situation, and...
Dialogue: 5,0:33:06.53,0:33:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not hard to see Eden of the East as a terrorist group.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:15.35,0:33:20.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're under arrest on suspicion of trespass and subversive activity!
Dialogue: 5,0:33:20.35,0:33:22.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come out with your hands up!
Dialogue: 5,0:33:24.31,0:33:26.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Panties?
Dialogue: 5,0:33:26.48,0:33:28.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Pan{\fscx164}-{\fscx82}
Dialogue: 5,0:33:30.89,0:33:35.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I prepared a hiding place just in case this happened.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:38.30,0:33:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over here.
Dialogue: 5,0:33:41.15,0:33:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that a bit cramped for two?
Dialogue: 5,0:33:49.80,0:33:51.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:29.24,0:34:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kasuga.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:30.50,0:34:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you dig this yourself?
Dialogue: 5,0:34:34.03,0:34:35.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an illusion.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:37.20,0:34:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is what I want to say, but this tunnel was dug far out to the east during
Dialogue: 5,0:34:41.39,0:34:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the revolutionary movements of the '60s, when the Red Army requested
Dialogue: 5,0:34:45.56,0:34:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the student movement's participation in the anti-Narita protests.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:51.31,0:34:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never thought I'd be saved by a tunnel the baby boomers dug for their protests.
Dialogue: 5,0:34:58.65,0:35:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's thrilling using the relics of that terrible generation to escape our enemies!
Dialogue: 5,0:35:06.35,0:35:12.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we need to take things like that and make them our own.
Dialogue: 5,0:35:29.54,0:35:31.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Glad to see you back, Takizawa.
Dialogue: 5,0:35:31.81,0:35:33.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tak!
Dialogue: 5,0:35:33.31,0:35:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while.
Dialogue: 5,0:35:35.34,0:35:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How've you been, Mittan?
Dialogue: 5,0:35:37.75,0:35:39.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name's not Mittan!
Dialogue: 5,0:35:39.69,0:35:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, you guys haven't changed at all.
Dialogue: 5,0:35:43.00,0:35:47.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is kinda sudden, but that semi's driver is on break.
Dialogue: 5,0:35:47.39,0:35:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you take this chance to drive it, Hirasawa?
Dialogue: 5,0:35:51.30,0:35:54.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That way even if the missiles do come, I loses too.
Dialogue: 5,0:35:54.68,0:35:55.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 5,0:35:55.66,0:35:57.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't drive trucks!
Dialogue: 5,0:35:58.15,0:36:00.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just did, so I'm sure you can figure it out.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:00.63,0:36:02.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 5,0:36:03.14,0:36:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right!
Dialogue: 5,0:36:04.05,0:36:08.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to have a CDL.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:19.47,0:36:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, hold on tight!
Dialogue: 5,0:36:29.45,0:36:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go! Follow me!
Dialogue: 5,0:36:31.50,0:36:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, where are we going?
Dialogue: 5,0:36:42.70,0:36:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to keep you waiting.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:45.52,0:36:48.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at the entrance without being too obvious.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:50.24,0:36:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a window in the storage room next to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:53.10,0:36:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can get away through there.
Dialogue: 5,0:36:55.89,0:36:59.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'm going first.
Dialogue: 5,0:37:52.92,0:37:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saki. I'll hold them off here, you follow her.
Dialogue: 5,0:37:59.00,0:38:05.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Takizawa is really Iinuma Seijiro's son, we might be able to turn things around.
Dialogue: 5,0:38:05.54,0:38:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you need to get her story somehow.
Dialogue: 5,0:38:09.43,0:38:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But{\fscx164}-{\fscx82}!
Dialogue: 5,0:38:10.97,0:38:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ohsugi!
Dialogue: 5,0:38:13.49,0:38:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 5,0:38:14.68,0:38:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saki!
Dialogue: 5,0:38:19.67,0:38:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Ohsugi.
Dialogue: 5,0:38:33.45,0:38:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, sir, we're closed{\fscx164}-{\fscx82}
Dialogue: 5,0:38:44.67,0:38:47.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So these are tomorrow's witnesses.
Dialogue: 5,0:38:47.38,0:38:50.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like it'll be pretty interesting.
Dialogue: 5,0:38:52.15,0:38:57.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mononobe pulled off a checkmate without even using his phone.
Dialogue: 5,0:38:58.80,0:39:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The NTA?
Dialogue: 5,0:39:02.19,0:39:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Terrible news, Tsuji!
Dialogue: 5,0:39:04.65,0:39:06.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The NTA auditors are onto us!
Dialogue: 5,0:39:11.59,0:39:13.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now you've done it.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:20.44,0:39:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 5,0:39:21.67,0:39:26.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You found the link between III and Mr. Outside?
Dialogue: 5,0:39:26.13,0:39:28.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not quite yet.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:28.17,0:39:29.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 5,0:39:29.22,0:39:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Checking out III's history, we found an order from a cafe in Shinbashi called Oda-Fuji.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:37.06,0:39:39.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And one from I earlier too.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:39.22,0:39:45.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cost of sending a message to the cafe Saizo frequents.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:45.57,0:39:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what was in there.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:56.75,0:39:58.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:39:58.45,0:40:00.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takizawa's too deeply involved in what he's doing.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:00.78,0:40:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go check it out.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:02.21,0:40:04.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Email me the detailed log.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:04.17,0:40:09.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hold it! It's too dangerous to go alone, we don't know what's there!
Dialogue: 5,0:40:09.95,0:40:12.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that happens, you'll have to handle the rest.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:12.95,0:40:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know I can leave Eden to you.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:15.72,0:40:17.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 5,0:40:17.11,0:40:18.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit being so gloomy!
Dialogue: 5,0:40:18.63,0:40:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Try to get along with Micchon.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:21.31,0:40:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's ticked that you hung up on her.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:38.80,0:40:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 5,0:40:45.54,0:40:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry. I took something.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:49.82,0:40:53.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this is you and Prime Minister Iinuma, isn't it.
Dialogue: 5,0:40:57.17,0:41:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And... You're pregnant in it.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:02.54,0:41:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was the baby inside you Takizawa?
Dialogue: 5,0:41:16.85,0:41:21.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His past is fading away.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:21.07,0:41:24.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if I know your past...
Dialogue: 5,0:41:24.03,0:41:27.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I can save him.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:27.10,0:41:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the public thinks he's a terrorist now,
Dialogue: 5,0:41:33.10,0:41:37.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if he's really Prime Minister Iinuma's son,
Dialogue: 5,0:41:37.01,0:41:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,maybe we can change things.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:41.38,0:41:43.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, tell me.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:43.42,0:41:46.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're Takizawa's mother, aren't you.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:54.82,0:41:57.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a nostalgic photo.
Dialogue: 5,0:41:59.10,0:42:07.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As far as I'm concerned, someone's age or status doesn't matter compared to their wallet.
Dialogue: 5,0:42:07.58,0:42:13.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you wanted to make me look bad, you could say that money is everything to me.
Dialogue: 5,0:42:14.54,0:42:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So if I taught my son anything...
Dialogue: 5,0:42:18.01,0:42:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's it.
Dialogue: 5,0:42:23.32,0:42:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he was abandoned with nothing but 500 yen.
Dialogue: 5,0:42:27.91,0:42:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what he thinks of that?
Dialogue: 5,0:42:31.52,0:42:34.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How does he think of money?
Dialogue: 5,0:42:37.07,0:42:43.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takizawa has the opportunity to spend ten billion yen freely.
Dialogue: 5,0:42:43.56,0:42:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 5,0:42:44.91,0:42:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't spent a single yen of it on himself.
Dialogue: 5,0:42:48.08,0:42:50.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the kind of person he is.
Dialogue: 5,0:42:50.84,0:42:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:42:54.42,0:42:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then he can't be my son.
Dialogue: 5,0:43:15.48,0:43:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll have to handle the rest yourself.
Dialogue: 5,0:43:31.74,0:43:33.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saki!
Dialogue: 5,0:43:35.52,0:43:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Aya wasn't Takizawa's mother?
Dialogue: 5,0:43:41.29,0:43:44.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, she is.
Dialogue: 5,0:43:44.97,0:43:48.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She knew he was left with 500 yen.
Dialogue: 5,0:44:38.67,0:44:40.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should probably call him.
Dialogue: 5,0:44:40.74,0:44:45.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell Takizawa I found his mother.
Dialogue: 5,0:44:45.97,0:44:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That it really is his mother.
Dialogue: 5,0:44:50.32,0:44:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So why are you hesitating?
Dialogue: 5,0:44:53.08,0:44:55.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I tell him...
Dialogue: 5,0:44:56.24,0:45:03.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I tell him, he'll never come back to me!
Dialogue: 5,0:45:06.77,0:45:08.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saki...
Dialogue: 5,0:45:12.29,0:45:15.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Don't give up!
Dialogue: 5,0:45:15.69,0:45:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go see Takizawa, and talk with him in person.
Dialogue: 5,0:45:20.40,0:45:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's waiting for you!
Dialogue: 5,0:45:35.30,0:45:36.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:45:36.71,0:45:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mean to bother you.
Dialogue: 5,0:45:42.94,0:45:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be seated.
Dialogue: 5,0:45:49.67,0:45:55.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You disappear at the airport, and then come back in a semi?
Dialogue: 5,0:45:55.45,0:45:57.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And in the trailer...
Dialogue: 5,0:45:57.64,0:46:02.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard it's what the government attacked yesterday night.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:02.31,0:46:04.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what are you doing?
Dialogue: 5,0:46:04.65,0:46:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without it, I won't be able to deal with this situation.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:10.43,0:46:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I brought it.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:13.08,0:46:15.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it is kind of inconvenient, though.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:15.93,0:46:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How audacious. You make quite the terrorist.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:20.68,0:46:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not a terrorist!
Dialogue: 5,0:46:23.30,0:46:25.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then what are you?
Dialogue: 5,0:46:27.53,0:46:30.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's kind of hard to explain.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:30.66,0:46:36.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To put it simply, I'm one of those chosen to improve this country...
Dialogue: 5,0:46:36.36,0:46:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Terrorists all say that.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:38.98,0:46:41.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, uh...
Dialogue: 5,0:46:41.54,0:46:43.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, this is tough.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:43.34,0:46:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do I explain it to you?
Dialogue: 5,0:46:45.61,0:46:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard quite enough already.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:49.26,0:46:53.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no intention of debating with you what you are and are not.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:53.85,0:46:58.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What I'd like to determine once and for all is what you're after.
Dialogue: 5,0:46:58.33,0:47:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why have you come here calling yourself Iinuma Seijiro's illegitimate son?
Dialogue: 5,0:47:04.11,0:47:05.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I want to know.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:05.77,0:47:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you after money?
Dialogue: 5,0:47:07.51,0:47:12.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or is this another of your terrorist plots?
Dialogue: 5,0:47:12.03,0:47:13.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 5,0:47:13.65,0:47:17.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't think I was Iinuma's son either.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:18.21,0:47:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's tough to put it into words properly.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:20.44,0:47:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just thought I'd become this country's king,
Dialogue: 5,0:47:23.76,0:47:28.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and support those who were having a hard time on their own.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:28.53,0:47:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One thing led to another, and now I'm on my way to becoming Prime Minister myself.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:34.08,0:47:38.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand what you're saying?
Dialogue: 5,0:47:39.45,0:47:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know what I'm talking about sounds unreasonable.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:43.81,0:47:46.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's true.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:49.32,0:47:53.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I want to be king if I don't have to or anything.
Dialogue: 5,0:47:53.13,0:48:00.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I were, I'd be responsible for everything, and everyone would complain to me.
Dialogue: 5,0:48:00.93,0:48:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd never be able to do it without wiping my memory.
Dialogue: 5,0:48:08.36,0:48:14.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I accept that there's something I can do.
Dialogue: 5,0:48:15.46,0:48:19.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He accepts becoming a king...
Dialogue: 5,0:48:21.96,0:48:30.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Iinuma thought he'd be able to enjoy the rest of his life after retiring from government,
Dialogue: 5,0:48:30.36,0:48:34.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he became Prime Minister again at the request of those around him.
Dialogue: 5,0:48:34.44,0:48:38.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even still, he wasn't able to do anything, and just passed on.
Dialogue: 5,0:48:40.34,0:48:48.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you are Iinuma's son, the road ahead won't be easy.
Dialogue: 5,0:48:48.65,0:48:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be even more powerless than you were as a terrorist.
Dialogue: 5,0:48:52.86,0:48:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:48:53.94,0:49:01.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I still can't give up until I teach the people who just keep on passing the buck a lesson.
Dialogue: 5,0:49:29.41,0:49:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mononobe?
Dialogue: 5,0:49:31.66,0:49:34.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How could he know{\fscx164}-{\fscx82}
Dialogue: 5,0:49:35.88,0:49:40.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mononobe? Maybe he's here to meet me.
Dialogue: 5,0:49:42.11,0:49:45.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I believe he said so.
Dialogue: 5,0:49:47.81,0:49:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I simply don't know what's happening.
Dialogue: 5,0:49:51.60,0:49:53.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 5,0:49:54.46,0:49:58.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well. Use the study.
Dialogue: 5,0:49:58.14,0:50:05.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But keep in mind, I'm participating in hearings about you tomorrow.
Dialogue: 5,0:50:05.51,0:50:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I'm entertaining the notion that you're Iinuma's illegitimate son...
Dialogue: 5,0:50:09.21,0:50:12.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I concealed you here...
Dialogue: 5,0:50:12.02,0:50:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I must accuse you of terrorism.
Dialogue: 5,0:50:16.72,0:50:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. That's okay.
Dialogue: 5,0:50:47.51,0:50:52.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he hasn't been seen in almost 30 years...
Dialogue: 5,0:51:04.08,0:51:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a tough one.
Dialogue: 5,0:51:06.41,0:51:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never expected even Juiz to take an interest.
Dialogue: 5,0:51:09.21,0:51:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you've managed to counter even my most indirect requests
Dialogue: 5,0:51:14.71,0:51:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and somehow turn things around.
Dialogue: 5,0:51:17.94,0:51:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've lost the game.
Dialogue: 5,0:51:21.85,0:51:23.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you just come here to say that?
Dialogue: 5,0:51:23.93,0:51:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because of that, I have a request for you, too.
Dialogue: 5,0:51:28.52,0:51:32.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we withdraw from this game?
Dialogue: 5,0:51:34.49,0:51:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even before I became a bureaucrat, I pondered what I'd like to do with this country.
Dialogue: 5,0:51:40.34,0:51:45.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But when it came to be, I found problem after problem piled up,
Dialogue: 5,0:51:45.00,0:51:50.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to the degree that even a bureaucrat's powers couldn't solve them legitimately.
Dialogue: 5,0:51:50.86,0:51:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I decided to wait for the government to destroy itself.
Dialogue: 5,0:51:55.60,0:51:59.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's when I got this.
Dialogue: 5,0:52:39.07,0:52:43.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Er... Are you Ato Saizo?
Dialogue: 5,0:52:49.31,0:52:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 5,0:52:52.50,0:52:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Hirasawa. A friend of IX.
Dialogue: 5,0:52:56.74,0:53:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to ask you something.
Dialogue: 5,0:53:18.69,0:53:20.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Young man.
Dialogue: 5,0:53:20.63,0:53:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If someone gave you ten billion yen and told you to improve this county, how would you use it?
Dialogue: 5,0:53:32.94,0:53:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you just pick the twelve Seleção from among your passengers?
Dialogue: 5,0:53:41.34,0:53:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Toshiko's such an inconvenience sometimes.
Dialogue: 5,0:53:46.56,0:53:47.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 5,0:53:47.91,0:53:49.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you need?
Dialogue: 5,0:53:51.19,0:53:57.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't intend to stop this game, no matter who asks, do you.
Dialogue: 5,0:53:57.21,0:54:01.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where does it even end?
Dialogue: 5,0:54:01.71,0:54:06.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Ato asked me how I'd spend 10 billion yen,
Dialogue: 5,0:54:06.76,0:54:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told him what this country needs is a diet.
Dialogue: 5,0:54:12.43,0:54:16.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have the government take the lead in distributing useful talent,
Dialogue: 5,0:54:16.30,0:54:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and focus only on fields which improve our standing in the world.
Dialogue: 5,0:54:20.65,0:54:27.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make the country leaner, more agile.
Dialogue: 5,0:54:28.64,0:54:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to achieve this swiftly, the government must be stripped to the bone.
Dialogue: 5,0:54:34.98,0:54:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this led you to that missile attack?
Dialogue: 5,0:54:37.41,0:54:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 5,0:54:38.78,0:54:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But really, I didn't even need missiles.
Dialogue: 5,0:54:42.25,0:54:47.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the country needs is one big shock.
Dialogue: 5,0:54:47.38,0:54:51.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, I've no need for some magic phone.
Dialogue: 5,0:54:51.51,0:54:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My connection and skill at negotiation will suffice.
Dialogue: 5,0:54:56.81,0:54:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, what I did...
Dialogue: 5,0:54:59.19,0:55:04.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your actions, and Yuuki's, fell neatly into my plan.
Dialogue: 5,0:55:04.79,0:55:06.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 5,0:55:11.16,0:55:14.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you tell me?
Dialogue: 5,0:55:14.60,0:55:19.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been busting myself thinking I'll be killed if I don't play along with the game,
Dialogue: 5,0:55:19.52,0:55:25.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but cooperating with other Seleção will let us come up with better ideas!
Dialogue: 5,0:55:25.84,0:55:29.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a bit too stubborn for that.
Dialogue: 5,0:55:30.69,0:55:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you should become Prime Minister, Mononobe.
Dialogue: 5,0:55:34.38,0:55:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a lot better fit for the job than I am, anyway.
Dialogue: 5,0:55:42.70,0:55:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm opening the gates.
Dialogue: 5,0:55:44.90,0:55:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one's looking, we'll be fine.
Dialogue: 5,0:55:50.25,0:55:51.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Takizawa?
Dialogue: 5,0:55:51.77,0:55:54.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He went in the mansion, and hasn't come out.
Dialogue: 5,0:55:54.47,0:55:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find his mother?
Dialogue: 5,0:55:57.90,0:56:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to tell him about it directly.
Dialogue: 5,0:56:04.10,0:56:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you become Prime Minister,
Dialogue: 5,0:56:07.25,0:56:12.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll happily quit this game and support you.
Dialogue: 5,0:56:12.64,0:56:18.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but I'm not interested in being a PM or a king.
Dialogue: 5,0:56:18.02,0:56:22.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The populace are nothing but a hundred million egoists.
Dialogue: 5,0:56:22.52,0:56:26.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should know that very well.
Dialogue: 5,0:56:28.71,0:56:33.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Modern Prime Ministers are nothing but scapegoats.
Dialogue: 5,0:56:33.12,0:56:38.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gaining freedom for themselves, they become only an outlet for the citizens who lack it.
Dialogue: 5,0:56:38.79,0:56:44.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even Iinuma Seijiro sacrificed himself to no avail.
Dialogue: 5,0:56:44.75,0:56:50.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how do you plan on making this country leaner and more agile?
Dialogue: 5,0:56:50.71,0:56:56.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First. Take the citizens' freedom without them realizing.
Dialogue: 5,0:56:56.49,0:56:58.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though they're so irresponsible and indecisive,
Dialogue: 5,0:56:58.95,0:57:04.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they hate having the will of others imposed on them.
Dialogue: 5,0:57:04.35,0:57:11.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, my first step in changing the country would be the revival of the Home Ministry.
Dialogue: 5,0:57:11.04,0:57:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Home Ministry?
Dialogue: 5,0:57:12.74,0:57:16.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't even know that, and you think you can be Prime Minister?
Dialogue: 5,0:57:27.47,0:57:28.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 5,0:57:29.62,0:57:31.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Takizawa?
Dialogue: 5,0:57:31.84,0:57:33.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saki?
Dialogue: 5,0:57:33.11,0:57:36.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I didn't call you yet.
Dialogue: 5,0:57:37.94,0:57:41.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about your mother.
Dialogue: 5,0:57:41.72,0:57:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How'd it go?
Dialogue: 5,0:57:43.24,0:57:50.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found her. The woman you mentioned really was your mother.
Dialogue: 5,0:57:50.72,0:57:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She runs a pub in Mishuku.
Dialogue: 5,0:57:53.54,0:57:54.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 5,0:57:54.82,0:57:56.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 5,0:57:56.33,0:58:00.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Her name's Iwashita Aya.
Dialogue: 5,0:58:00.88,0:58:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think she was Prime Minister Iinuma's mistress when he was only an MP.
Dialogue: 5,0:58:05.04,0:58:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She said he paid her rent at the hotel in New York.
Dialogue: 5,0:58:12.73,0:58:17.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think she lived there twenty years ago.
Dialogue: 5,0:58:18.37,0:58:23.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found a picture of her in New York with Prime Minister Iinuma while she was pregnant, too.
Dialogue: 5,0:58:23.97,0:58:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you really are his son.
Dialogue: 5,0:59:00.86,0:59:02.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,0:59:06.43,0:59:10.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why I remembered New York.
Dialogue: 5,0:59:11.04,0:59:14.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you now, Saki?
Dialogue: 5,0:59:14.03,0:59:17.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right outside the front door. I'm with Micchon and the others.
Dialogue: 5,0:59:24.49,0:59:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see you, Saki.
Dialogue: 5,0:59:28.88,0:59:30.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takizawa...
Dialogue: 5,0:59:30.37,0:59:34.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad I found my past.
Dialogue: 5,0:59:34.04,0:59:38.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I understand what my mom's like now.
Dialogue: 5,0:59:38.71,0:59:40.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Saki.
Dialogue: 5,0:59:50.85,0:59:53.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like you have your past back.
Dialogue: 5,0:59:53.93,0:59:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how does it feel being the Prime Minister's son?
Dialogue: 5,0:59:58.31,1:00:01.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You knew, Mononobe?
Dialogue: 5,1:00:02.46,1:00:05.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't feel real at all.
Dialogue: 5,1:00:05.35,1:00:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's get back to the real issue.
Dialogue: 5,1:00:08.53,1:00:15.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give you a budget equal to the money left on your phone.
Dialogue: 5,1:00:15.56,1:00:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And there's no need to worry about the Supporter anymore.
Dialogue: 5,1:00:18.43,1:00:21.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll also remove your friends from suspicion.
Dialogue: 5,1:00:21.65,1:00:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In return, you disappear off to somewhere.
Dialogue: 5,1:00:27.32,1:00:29.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds pretty good.
Dialogue: 5,1:00:32.00,1:00:34.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's one thing I'd like to ask, though.
Dialogue: 5,1:00:34.31,1:00:37.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you talk about the citizens...
Dialogue: 5,1:00:37.22,1:00:40.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do they mean to you?
Dialogue: 5,1:00:40.33,1:00:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a silly question.
Dialogue: 5,1:00:41.92,1:00:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Citizens are nothing more than parts for improving the nation.
Dialogue: 5,1:00:47.42,1:00:51.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're nothing to be concerned about individually.
Dialogue: 5,1:00:51.14,1:00:56.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But they're each individuals who want to become someone.
Dialogue: 5,1:00:56.79,1:00:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's just an inconvenience.
Dialogue: 5,1:00:59.34,1:01:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible for everyone to become someone.
Dialogue: 5,1:01:04.45,1:01:07.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may be right...
Dialogue: 5,1:01:07.22,1:01:13.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But expressing their individuality makes them stronger.
Dialogue: 5,1:01:13.00,1:01:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I hadn't been told I was one of the few chosen to save Japan, I don't think I'd ever have come this far.
Dialogue: 5,1:01:21.63,1:01:27.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I feel like your methods just don't have enough love.
Dialogue: 5,1:01:28.52,1:01:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're turning down my offer?
Dialogue: 5,1:01:32.25,1:01:41.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe. Just once, I want to broadcast my demands to the whole country like a proper terrorist.
Dialogue: 5,1:01:42.67,1:01:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At first I thought I'd become a king or something, but it looks like there's no time for that.
Dialogue: 5,1:01:50.43,1:01:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not for a nobody like me, just like when I was standing in front of the White House.
Dialogue: 5,1:01:57.98,1:01:59.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Juiz speaking.
Dialogue: 5,1:01:59.76,1:02:04.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Juiz. I'd like to make a phone call to everyone in the country.
Dialogue: 5,1:02:04.53,1:02:05.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you do it?
Dialogue: 5,1:02:06.21,1:02:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The phone bill for that will be huge.
Dialogue: 5,1:02:10.26,1:02:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's quite possible that it'll take every yen you have.
Dialogue: 5,1:02:15.20,1:02:17.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you still want to?
Dialogue: 5,1:02:17.15,1:02:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's inconvenient.
Dialogue: 5,1:02:19.64,1:02:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you leave me just a hundred million yen?
Dialogue: 5,1:02:23.57,1:02:27.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a very tall order.
Dialogue: 5,1:02:27.44,1:02:29.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 5,1:02:31.27,1:02:34.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know! I can use that!
Dialogue: 5,1:02:36.21,1:02:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you tell me one thing?
Dialogue: 5,1:02:38.06,1:02:42.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you asked Takizawa how he'd spend 10 billion yen, how did he respond?
Dialogue: 5,1:02:44.48,1:02:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't ask him that.
Dialogue: 5,1:02:54.89,1:02:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could I have one paper?
Dialogue: 5,1:02:59.78,1:03:01.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 5,1:03:07.97,1:03:13.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about the money. The people who only want one are the people who really want to read it.
Dialogue: 5,1:03:14.75,1:03:17.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you sell them one by one?
Dialogue: 5,1:03:17.77,1:03:21.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, I make enough off the people who aren't gonna read.
Dialogue: 5,1:03:21.47,1:03:25.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's pretty tough to get them to pay up, though.
Dialogue: 5,1:03:25.48,1:03:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess.
Dialogue: 5,1:03:31.65,1:03:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, boy. Why are you delivering newspapers this late?
Dialogue: 5,1:03:39.84,1:03:43.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's practice for earning money.
Dialogue: 5,1:03:46.83,1:03:49.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People are funny.
Dialogue: 5,1:03:49.24,1:03:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even a five-year-old knows how to spend money,
Dialogue: 5,1:03:52.56,1:03:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but there's plenty of adults who don't know how to earn it.
Dialogue: 5,1:03:56.07,1:04:00.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They feel better handing over money than bowing their head and taking it.
Dialogue: 5,1:04:00.35,1:04:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They go on and on about how the customer's always right, always the winner,
Dialogue: 5,1:04:06.04,1:04:09.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but isn't that supposed to be how the seller feels, not them?
Dialogue: 5,1:04:10.35,1:04:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 5,1:04:12.07,1:04:18.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if everyone's spending, who's left to provide the service?
Dialogue: 5,1:04:20.06,1:04:27.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think a society where people prefer earning to spending is a healthier one.
Dialogue: 5,1:04:29.57,1:04:34.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that's why you chose him as a Seleção?
Dialogue: 5,1:04:36.34,1:04:42.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, because you were curious why he thought that way?
Dialogue: 5,1:04:44.88,1:04:49.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like we'll never agree.
Dialogue: 5,1:04:49.63,1:04:54.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? I think we look at things the same way.
Dialogue: 5,1:04:55.24,1:04:57.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do as you will.
Dialogue: 5,1:05:05.83,1:05:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 5,1:05:11.25,1:05:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master! A message from Juiz!
Dialogue: 5,1:05:14.65,1:05:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What!?
Dialogue: 5,1:05:16.53,1:05:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like your aid in completing one of IX's requests.
Dialogue: 5,1:05:19.86,1:05:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vintage!?
Dialogue: 5,1:05:21.18,1:05:29.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I want to use AirShip to connect Eden of the East to every cell phone in Japan.
Dialogue: 5,1:05:29.28,1:05:34.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is he up to now?
Dialogue: 5,1:06:00.14,1:06:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's from Tak.
Dialogue: 5,1:06:02.14,1:06:04.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master! It's here!
Dialogue: 5,1:06:59.60,1:07:02.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, everyone.
Dialogue: 5,1:07:02.45,1:07:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the Air King, perpetrator of the terrorist attacks beginning with Careless Monday, Takizawa Akira.
Dialogue: 5,1:07:12.94,1:07:19.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yesterday I proclaimed myself Prime Minister Iinuma's son in order to get your attention,
Dialogue: 5,1:07:19.72,1:07:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but to tell the truth, I have absolutely no connection to the late Prime Minister.
Dialogue: 5,1:07:25.51,1:07:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to apologize from the depths of my heart to his relations for this.
Dialogue: 5,1:07:35.40,1:07:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's Tak doing? Is he just going to waste Saki's hard work?
Dialogue: 5,1:07:42.86,1:07:45.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, to get to the point.
Dialogue: 5,1:07:46.01,1:07:51.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm announcing my next terrorist plot, so everyone pay attention.
Dialogue: 5,1:07:52.19,1:07:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll take another mass of youth off to paradise.
Dialogue: 5,1:07:58.94,1:08:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This time, far more than the 20,000 of half a year ago.
Dialogue: 5,1:08:05.20,1:08:11.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This country will lose the workers who form the basis of its future!
Dialogue: 5,1:08:11.92,1:08:14.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To avoid this...
Dialogue: 5,1:08:14.06,1:08:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must comply with my demand.
Dialogue: 5,1:08:19.19,1:08:22.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's playing the Pied Piper again?
Dialogue: 5,1:08:22.11,1:08:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's he trying to do?
Dialogue: 5,1:08:24.31,1:08:27.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only one thing will satisfy me.
Dialogue: 5,1:08:28.17,1:08:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the old men convinced they're successful need to throw away everything they clutch to themselves!
Dialogue: 5,1:08:34.86,1:08:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show us you have the will to journey with us to a new paradise!
Dialogue: 5,1:08:40.81,1:08:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my demand.
Dialogue: 5,1:08:44.98,1:08:50.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you don't accept, the values of today will be wiped away,
Dialogue: 5,1:08:50.01,1:08:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the paradise you dreamed of will disappear.
Dialogue: 5,1:08:54.19,1:08:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The previous missile attacks were nothing but practice for this day.
Dialogue: 5,1:09:00.10,1:09:06.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you ignore my demands, something even more fearsome will befall this country.
Dialogue: 5,1:09:06.27,1:09:10.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if you listen at all to what I have to say,
Dialogue: 5,1:09:11.30,1:09:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,something wonderful is waiting for you.
Dialogue: 5,1:09:17.27,1:09:24.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, I'm giving each and every one of you one yen worth of e-money.
Dialogue: 5,1:09:24.51,1:09:27.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think of it as a parting gift
Dialogue: 5,1:09:27.66,1:09:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and as proof that what I've said is true.
Dialogue: 5,1:09:31.86,1:09:34.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A promissory note of sorts.
Dialogue: 5,1:09:36.73,1:09:44.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Juiz. Give each phone I'm connected to now one yen of e-money.
Dialogue: 5,1:09:45.75,1:09:47.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 5,1:09:47.86,1:09:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May you continue to be a beloved king, instilling hope and fear in your subjects.
Dialogue: 5,1:10:15.29,1:10:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Very well!
Dialogue: 5,1:10:16.48,1:10:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,NEETs who have locked yourselves in your rooms!
Dialogue: 5,1:10:20.46,1:10:22.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's your turn now!
Dialogue: 5,1:10:22.98,1:10:28.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Using AirShip, assemble at the promised land, the Eden of the East!
Dialogue: 5,1:10:28.00,1:10:29.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be waiting.
Dialogue: 5,1:10:34.37,1:10:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's he thinking!?
Dialogue: 5,1:10:36.60,1:10:40.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if he makes some clever points, a political argument isn't enough to get them going!
Dialogue: 5,1:10:41.27,1:10:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once, we too tried recklessly to improve this country.
Dialogue: 5,1:10:48.11,1:10:54.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking back on it now, we call our actions mistaken.
Dialogue: 5,1:10:55.72,1:11:02.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But back then, we were amateurs who didn't know our left from our right.
Dialogue: 5,1:11:04.12,1:11:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If what we did was wrong, then what was right?
Dialogue: 5,1:11:14.41,1:11:18.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, even though we'd though we'd changed so little,
Dialogue: 5,1:11:18.65,1:11:22.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the rules of the world changed so much.
Dialogue: 5,1:11:22.49,1:11:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The idea that this country needed new ideas before it sank deeper came to the fore.
Dialogue: 5,1:11:30.60,1:11:35.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it means that even though telling the older generation to accept this seems cruel,
Dialogue: 5,1:11:35.27,1:11:42.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,in the end, you need to ask them to give up their power and hand over responsibility.
Dialogue: 5,1:11:42.76,1:11:47.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even Japan's beloved Sakamoto Ryoma and Shirasu Jiro
Dialogue: 5,1:11:47.87,1:11:54.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,just avoided being dirtied by choosing their fights carefully.
Dialogue: 5,1:11:54.70,1:12:02.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The true saviors of this country are those unknowns who, simply by virtue of steadily living their daily lives
Dialogue: 5,1:12:02.31,1:12:07.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,became the bloodied losers of history.
Dialogue: 5,1:12:07.05,1:12:12.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In front of a society which subconsciously loathes this concept,
Dialogue: 5,1:12:12.41,1:12:17.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,IX takes the risk of becoming a scapegoat.
Dialogue: 5,1:12:18.20,1:12:20.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting.
Dialogue: 5,1:12:21.53,1:12:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's time to drop the curtain on this game for now.
Dialogue: 5,1:12:25.58,1:12:27.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've chosen a winner.
Dialogue: 5,1:12:35.27,1:12:39.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did that phone call really go to everyone in Japan?
Dialogue: 5,1:12:39.33,1:12:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I think.
Dialogue: 5,1:12:42.95,1:12:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to cause you so much trouble.
Dialogue: 5,1:12:45.08,1:12:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be running away as a terrorist now. Good luck at the hearing.
Dialogue: 5,1:12:51.48,1:12:54.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand. Farewell.
Dialogue: 5,1:13:02.33,1:13:04.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. Here.
Dialogue: 5,1:13:05.68,1:13:08.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think you even need to see it, though.
Dialogue: 5,1:13:16.14,1:13:20.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He does rather remind me of the master.
Dialogue: 5,1:13:20.62,1:13:24.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 5,1:13:24.07,1:13:25.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 5,1:13:25.55,1:13:29.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you think so, I don't mind.
Dialogue: 5,1:13:33.34,1:13:38.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You always make such drastic decisions.
Dialogue: 5,1:13:38.10,1:13:42.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this country's people are amazingly cynical.
Dialogue: 5,1:13:42.83,1:13:47.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't hold your breath hoping they'll get the message.
Dialogue: 5,1:13:47.55,1:13:50.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that a rather lonely point of view?
Dialogue: 5,1:13:50.15,1:13:52.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe, but it's reality.
Dialogue: 5,1:14:00.27,1:14:01.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mononobe!
Dialogue: 5,1:14:05.82,1:14:08.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Seleção.
Dialogue: 5,1:14:08.88,1:14:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Mr. Outside.
Dialogue: 5,1:14:12.29,1:14:18.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This may be sudden, but with this phone call, the current game comes to a close.
Dialogue: 5,1:14:18.49,1:14:22.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm satisfied with the progress I've seen from you.
Dialogue: 5,1:14:22.76,1:14:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Therefore, you're all winners.
Dialogue: 5,1:14:27.37,1:14:34.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I look forward to seeing you develop into people whose talents can change Japan for the better.
Dialogue: 5,1:14:34.10,1:14:38.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've always been that kind of person anyway.
Dialogue: 5,1:14:40.66,1:14:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As thanks for participating in my game to the very end,
Dialogue: 5,1:14:44.99,1:14:47.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a wonderful present for you all.
Dialogue: 5,1:14:48.45,1:14:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you all to have this.
Dialogue: 5,1:14:51.88,1:14:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bonus I prepared for you Seleção in advance.
Dialogue: 5,1:15:00.42,1:15:03.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noblesse oblige.
Dialogue: 5,1:15:04.43,1:15:11.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May you continue to be this country's potential messiahs.
Dialogue: 5,1:15:11.23,1:15:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Potential?
Dialogue: 5,1:15:38.43,1:15:42.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it! Not me!
Dialogue: 5,1:15:59.66,1:16:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Saizo.
Dialogue: 5,1:16:04.22,1:16:06.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Farewell.
Dialogue: 5,1:16:21.54,1:16:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A present? What is it?
Dialogue: 5,1:16:25.52,1:16:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I gave them their phones,
Dialogue: 5,1:16:28.11,1:16:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I left one little trap waiting.
Dialogue: 5,1:16:32.41,1:16:36.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This will free them from the game completely.
Dialogue: 5,1:16:38.55,1:16:43.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just how much do you intend to play with people's lives!?
Dialogue: 5,1:16:47.03,1:16:50.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not old enough to lose to you kids yet.
Dialogue: 5,1:17:35.62,1:17:37.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tak!
Dialogue: 5,1:17:37.43,1:17:39.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takizawa!
Dialogue: 5,1:17:41.71,1:17:44.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Takizawa!
Dialogue: 5,1:18:02.35,1:18:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 5,1:18:04.38,1:18:08.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard there's a man named Takizawa here.
Dialogue: 5,1:18:09.90,1:18:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mononobe!
Dialogue: 5,1:18:11.54,1:18:14.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 5,1:18:14.09,1:18:16.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're in my way.
Dialogue: 5,1:18:17.27,1:18:22.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you remember me after all I've done for you!?
Dialogue: 5,1:18:49.57,1:18:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if that sound didn't work on me because I already wiped my own memory?
Dialogue: 5,1:18:56.68,1:19:01.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Never mind that. What are you doing calling everyone in Japan and telling them that, Tak!?
Dialogue: 5,1:19:03.47,1:19:06.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. It'll work out fine.
Dialogue: 5,1:19:08.76,1:19:13.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure they'll understand what you were trying to tell them.
Dialogue: 5,1:19:13.72,1:19:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Saki.
Dialogue: 5,1:19:22.30,1:19:25.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if Mom was paying attention?
Dialogue: 5,1:19:39.24,1:19:40.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really!?
Dialogue: 5,1:19:40.90,1:19:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a mom.
Dialogue: 5,1:19:42.84,1:19:46.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pushing it that far.
Dialogue: 5,1:19:51.45,1:19:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Tak really isn't the PM's illegitimate son!?
Dialogue: 5,1:19:56.00,1:19:57.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks that way.
Dialogue: 5,1:19:57.82,1:20:01.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But at least I'm not causing any trouble for Chigusa this way.
Dialogue: 5,1:20:01.69,1:20:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you really are a terrorist, then, Tak?
Dialogue: 5,1:20:06.92,1:20:09.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't this dangerous?
Dialogue: 5,1:20:09.06,1:20:13.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! What will everyone think!?
Dialogue: 5,1:20:13.20,1:20:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I guess...
Dialogue: 5,1:20:19.09,1:20:21.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I'm going.
Dialogue: 5,1:20:22.51,1:20:25.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Going? Where?
Dialogue: 5,1:20:25.08,1:20:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you realize why Saki came here!?
Dialogue: 5,1:20:30.31,1:20:31.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takizawa...
Dialogue: 5,1:20:32.17,1:20:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 5,1:20:34.29,1:20:35.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 5,1:20:35.92,1:20:42.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I remembered one last thing I have to so.
Dialogue: 5,1:20:42.05,1:20:46.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as I'm done with that, I'll come back to you.
Dialogue: 5,1:20:49.54,1:20:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See ya.
Dialogue: 5,1:20:51.74,1:20:56.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell Hirasawa, Itazu, and Kasuga thanks for me.
Dialogue: 5,1:21:33.56,1:21:35.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'd better come back.
Dialogue: 5,1:21:35.79,1:21:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Promise me.
Dialogue: 5,1:21:38.41,1:21:41.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure. I'll come back.
Dialogue: 5,1:22:00.75,1:22:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that was the last we saw of Takizawa.
Dialogue: 5,1:22:08.06,1:22:13.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After he announced his terrorist plot and the Seleção game ended,
Dialogue: 5,1:22:13.67,1:22:18.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,his wish to become a king was wiped away too.
Dialogue: 5,1:22:19.85,1:22:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So Takizawa is still surrounded with mysteries.
Dialogue: 5,1:22:27.33,1:22:33.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there are still a few people who want him to become a king.
Dialogue: 5,1:22:33.76,1:22:35.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Chigusa.
Dialogue: 5,1:22:36.26,1:22:40.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Takizawa and the PM had no blood relation,
Dialogue: 5,1:22:40.39,1:22:47.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but in their short conversation she saw in him her husband's determination.
Dialogue: 5,1:22:50.49,1:22:56.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Aya, who implicitly admitted that Takizawa was her son.
Dialogue: 5,1:22:56.95,1:23:00.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Along with the dog, she disappeared again.
Dialogue: 5,1:23:01.37,1:23:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's probably trying to hide away the secret of Takizawa's birth.
Dialogue: 5,1:23:21.03,1:23:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The NEETs who Takizawa gathered
Dialogue: 5,1:23:24.73,1:23:33.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,run a co-op flea market at the shopping mall they consider a holy land along with the AKX20000.
Dialogue: 5,1:23:34.53,1:23:39.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sadly, Takizawa hasn't appeared there for them.
Dialogue: 5,1:23:39.56,1:23:46.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though they resent the Air King, they wait every day for his return.
Dialogue: 5,1:23:47.21,1:23:52.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, as for the old men who responded to his demand,
Dialogue: 5,1:23:52.15,1:23:57.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at first they followed Takizawa's demands and went to meet with the NEETs,
Dialogue: 5,1:23:57.42,1:24:03.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And some companies announced a hiring war, but neither lasted long.
Dialogue: 5,1:24:03.93,1:24:08.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, the majority of the NEETs took up jobs,
Dialogue: 5,1:24:08.41,1:24:12.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and made that place into a paradise of new financial activity.
Dialogue: 5,1:24:12.86,1:24:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They've made Japan a little brighter.
Dialogue: 5,1:24:17.32,1:24:21.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For us, who were cast as the villains,
Dialogue: 5,1:24:21.60,1:24:27.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,society's judgment was too harsh, and for a time we were forced to close Eden as a company.
Dialogue: 5,1:24:29.32,1:24:35.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Afterwards, under Hirasawa and Itazu's leadership,
Dialogue: 5,1:24:35.14,1:24:42.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they moved to Toyosu and lived communally while working on a more user-friendly system.
Dialogue: 5,1:24:44.66,1:24:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been half a year now.
Dialogue: 5,1:24:47.59,1:24:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still haven't seen any big changes in the country.
Dialogue: 5,1:24:54.25,1:25:00.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's changing somehow in places I can't see.
Dialogue: 5,1:25:01.17,1:25:03.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe this.
Dialogue: 5,1:25:12.24,1:25:20.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And somewhere in this city, Takizawa believes it too and is working hard to make it happen.
Dialogue: 5,1:25:27.53,1:25:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pouring his heart and soul into everyone's hopes.
Dialogue: 5,1:30:22.61,1:30:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Young man.
Dialogue: 5,1:30:24.23,1:30:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If someone gave you ten billion yen and told you to improve this county, how would you use it?
Dialogue: 5,1:30:32.58,1:30:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Back to that again?
Dialogue: 5,1:30:37.78,1:30:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've finally found you, Mr. Outside.
Dialogue: 5,1:30:50.69,1:30:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 5,1:30:55.47,1:30:58.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit playing senile!
Dialogue: 5,1:30:58.35,1:31:02.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you say we'd automatically meet you when we won the game?
Dialogue: 5,1:31:02.05,1:31:04.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should keep your promises!
Dialogue: 5,1:31:17.40,1:31:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, that's good enough.
Dialogue: 5,1:31:20.02,1:31:22.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're even now.
Dialogue: 5,1:31:22.81,1:31:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, there's some things I need you to do for me.
Dialogue: 5,1:31:27.50,1:31:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just for starters, how about turning right at this next intersection?
Dialogue: 5,1:31:34.01,1:31:38.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's still lots of things we need to do.
Dialogue: 5,1:31:38.56,1:31:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, stop acting like you've gone senile!
Dialogue: 5,1:31:44.98,1:31:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the story of the eleven days I spent with Takizawa.
